  "elapsed_s": 11.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Two people stood on top of-- on each side of the door, and picked up a bag of cement with their two-- two hands and put it on the back of the person who was standing under the door.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "On his back, he was carrying it 50 meters or whatever it took to, to the machine.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then there was somebody there who had a razor or a knife or something, opened up the bag on one end, and you had to tilt your shoulders and pour it into, into a huge, big cavity there, which after funneled it down to the mixer.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And so by the end of the day, we had to unload one, one truck a day, which, which normally if a person is well-fed and properly fed is not-- between all those people, it's not such a great deal.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But being not fed normally and being on, on a ration of one quarter of a bread-- a loaf of bread is about that big, and then about one fifth of a loaf, and then one sixth of a loaf, because rations were getting smaller and smaller.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It wasn't an easy task to carry 50 kilo.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But the 50 kilo, to carry the bag was easier.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That was the easy part of the job.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Somebody collects this as finished.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There's no, no, no second chance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was just taken away and end of the story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So everybody wanted to make sure that he got home, marched back to the camp, which didn't always happen because they didn't always make it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But the more unpleasant part of the job was to stand in the truck and hand down, hand down and put it on people's shoulder the bag, because the cement bags are very rough.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
